title: MarcusMK
author: MarcusMK
content: Brand new Setup.Went to the "Pools" tab, entered my BRAIINS details, needed 3 attempts until it would save, now has those details saved. But, when I go to Miner dashboard, under "Pools", it says the URL is etc.viabtc.com:333 with Username port forwarded.futurebitWhy are my details not showing up and my hash seemingly going to future bit?Thank you for your help.

comments.author: BitDane
comments.body: It looks like that the miner is not configured properly. It is also possible that the miner is configured different pool by default and that what you think that you have saved the edited configuration did not happen.You can try to troubleshoot the problem by:Double checking the data input on the configuration, check if the are URL, username and password is correct.Make sure that you saved the configurationYou can also try to restart your minerAnd also check the miner documentation to see if there is a specific instruction in configuring the miner to use another pool.You can also check this board[1] to see if there is any guide in there that can help you.[1] https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?board=14.0

comments.author: altair_tech
comments.body: Try opening in a new browser or in incognito mode. Sometimes browser caching causes these issues.
